sdp/verification/t-012@20260408t223256z-verify.md:8:The implementation satisfies the spec for discovery behavior: it parses `tailscale status --json`, iterates online peers, probes `http://{ip}:8443/federation/v1/identity`, validates identity payload shape, and returns `PeerInfo` for valid peers. Registry persistence is implemented at `~/.promptclaw/federation/peers.json` with requested fields and merge semantics (online updates + offline carry-forward). `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` includes coverage for happy path, missing tailscale, no promptclaw peers, malformed identity, self-IP exclusion, persistence, and merge behavior.
sdp/verification/t-012@20260408t223256z-verify.md:11:Core acceptance criteria are covered by unit tests and implementation. One gap is lifecycle wiring: this change introduces discovery and registry utilities but does not show an orchestrator/scheduler call site that periodically invokes discovery and writes the merged registry, so end-to-end federation behavior is only partially exercised by tests.
