sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zb-verify.md:71:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-25T19:48:10.007Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777146490007_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-001 @20260425t183959zb-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-001 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260425T183959Zb_1777146438.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-25\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py`\n- `tests/test_sampler_buffers.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `on_sampler_free` correctly fulfills the requirements. It sends the `/b_free` OSC message to scsynth with the correct buffer ID and clears the `buffer_id` on the `BufferRecord`. The method correctly returns early if `buffer_id` is `None`, ensuring idempotent behavior.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete for the requested scope. Unit tests cover:\n- Successful buffer release and ID clearing.\n- No-op behavior when `buffer_id` is already `None`.\n- Idempotency (multiple calls only send one `/b_free`).\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows the established patterns in `sampler_buffers.py` and uses the `OSCSender` protocol correctly. Docstrings and type hints are consistent with the existing codebase.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets were identified. The implementation uses a simple OSC message with an integer argument, which is safe.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, concise, and well-documented. The tests are exhaustive for the logic implemented.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found. Note: A `PermissionError` was observed in `tests/test_daemon_fallback.py` during the full test suite run, but this is unrelated to the changes in T-001 and is attributed to macOS Seatbelt restrictions on the CI environment (attempting to write to `/Users/anthony/.promptclaw/pets.json`).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe `on_sampler_free` implementation is solid. The next slice of T-001 (LRU eviction) can proceed. Hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified as pre-existing in the startup flow.\n"}}
