sdp/verification/t-019@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:70:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T18:46:24.824Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777315584824_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-019 @20260427t001208zb-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-019 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260427T001208Zb_1777315522.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-27\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py`\n- `tests/test_usage_journal.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `_derive_source_kind` correctly follows the priority order specified in the requirements:\n1. `sample_origin` (explicit metadata or scene metadata)\n2. `generated_by` (metadata or scene metadata) -> \"generated\"\n3. `library_path` (metadata or scene metadata) -> \"library\"\n4. Sensible default -> \"gesture\"\n\nThis logic is correctly integrated into `record_scheduled_sample_event` and the resulting `source_kind` is persisted via `tracker.record_play` into the `SamplePlay` dataclass.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete. All branches of the `source_kind` derivation logic are covered by new unit tests in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`. Edge cases such as scene-level metadata fallback and explicit origin priority are also verified.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code changes are consistent with existing patterns in `usage_journal.py`. The use of `metadata.get()` and `scene_metadata.get()` matches the established style for attribute extraction from event objects.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or sensitive data exposures were identified. The changes are confined to metadata derivation and persistence in a local journal file.\n\n## Quality\nThe implementation is clean and follows Python's idiomatic practices. The unit tests are descriptive and provide high confidence in the behavioral correctness of the new feature.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found. (Note: Pre-existing environmental permission issues in the full test suite were observed but are unrelated to this task and documented in ESCALATIONS.md).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe derivation logic and tests are well-implemented. The backward compatibility with legacy aliases in `SamplePlay` and `JournalEntry` remains intact.\n"}}
